00:08:15.580 --> 00:08:18.830
&gt;&gt; We sat there and
watched the day go by.

00:08:18.830 --> 00:08:21.460
We didn't even attempt
to say a word.

00:08:21.460 --> 00:08:25.680
I realized then that she
and I needed no words.

00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:29.800
In the afternoon that
day, it began to rain.

00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:32.230
I dragged her out of the house.

00:08:32.230 --> 00:08:34.900
We jumped in the rain,
begging it to pour on us

00:08:34.900 --> 00:08:38.950
so we could be tall,
big, strong and bold.

00:08:38.950 --> 00:08:43.020
In that moment, my sister returned.

00:08:43.020 --> 00:08:46.200
She smiled and laughed.

00:08:46.200 --> 00:08:49.400
That day we began to form
new childhood memories,

00:08:49.400 --> 00:08:54.130
filling the void left by the
one that had been wiped out.

00:08:54.130 --> 00:08:57.480
We lay on the ground,
stretched out our arms and legs,

00:08:57.480 --> 00:09:02.960 position:56%
rain falling on our faces and felt
free but my mother had seen us laugh

00:09:02.960 --> 00:09:05.540
and jump, and thought that this
thing was going to come again.

00:09:05.540 --> 00:09:09.730
The following day, the entire
village gathered outside

00:09:09.730 --> 00:09:15.750
of our house for yet another
[inaudible] to cure my sister.

00:09:15.750 --> 00:09:17.440
She had been through
all these rituals

00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:20.390
and [inaudible] and
nothing had changed.

00:09:20.390 --> 00:09:25.420 position:56%
Each time, [inaudible] promised that
she would be healed within days.

00:09:25.420 --> 00:09:28.330
There was once, at least
according to the elders,

00:09:28.330 --> 00:09:32.120
a glimpse of the [inaudible]
healing, the [inaudible]

00:09:32.120 --> 00:09:36.420 position:56%
that had been put in the [inaudible]
for the ancestors to take at night

00:09:36.420 --> 00:09:41.890
in one of the many rituals were
not there by morning leading them

00:09:41.890 --> 00:09:45.190
to believe that the
ancestors had healed her.

00:09:45.190 --> 00:09:50.150
It was not long after that,
that this thing again proving

00:09:50.150 --> 00:09:53.050 position:56%
that the [inaudible] had simply been
stolen by thieves, that it returned.

00:09:53.050 --> 00:09:59.090
The day of the ritual I remember
how the clouds moved across the sky

00:09:59.090 --> 00:10:03.520
in a hurry and how thick fog hung
onto the grass, the mountains,

00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:07.120
the riverbanks and forest
as if to announce death.

00:10:07.120 --> 00:10:10.450
It hung so low that people
appeared to be floating

00:10:10.450 --> 00:10:12.890
with their legs cut
off below their knees.

00:10:12.890 --> 00:10:16.140
The women's chatter and songs
reached us long before the crowd

00:10:16.140 --> 00:10:17.440
was visible.

00:10:17.440 --> 00:10:20.080
It appeared as if the
fog had swallowed them

00:10:20.080 --> 00:10:22.570
and that the women would
never come into sight.

00:10:22.570 --> 00:10:24.770
All the same, they did.

00:10:24.770 --> 00:10:29.280
They [inaudible] and chanted
song as they approached our home.

00:10:29.280 --> 00:10:34.820
Men came in silence, arms folded
behind their back carrying sticks.

00:10:34.820 --> 00:10:38.580 position:56%
A few minutes after the women
arrived, smoke escaped the fireplace

00:10:38.580 --> 00:10:41.340
into the sky, dancing
with the moving clouds

00:10:41.340 --> 00:10:44.740 position:56%
as if the sky was their dance floor.

00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:48.100
The children ran around and kicked
soccer balls that had been made

00:10:48.100 --> 00:10:51.430
by stuffing papers
into plastic bags.

00:10:51.430 --> 00:10:54.380
Everyone moved in a
chaotic choreography.

00:10:54.380 --> 00:10:57.460
That way went an [inaudible]
woman carrying a bucket of water

00:10:57.460 --> 00:11:00.930
on her head, this way went
a child with a tablecloth,

00:11:00.930 --> 00:11:04.660
that way went a dog with a
bone, this way went chickens,

00:11:04.660 --> 00:11:07.350
that way stood women
gossiping about my sister.

00:11:07.350 --> 00:11:11.930
From our house, I could
see the crowds amplifying

00:11:11.930 --> 00:11:14.220
as more people arrived.

00:11:14.220 --> 00:11:17.130
I looked at my sister and
found her face as it had been

00:11:17.130 --> 00:11:20.400
in earlier months, emotionless.

00:11:20.400 --> 00:11:24.740
In the past few days she had given
me hope that she had returned.

00:11:24.740 --> 00:11:27.620
Now, tears rolled down our cheeks.

00:11:27.620 --> 00:11:31.620
I knew then that she still felt
something, that the last few days

00:11:31.620 --> 00:11:33.800
of holding hands, laughing
and jumping

00:11:33.800 --> 00:11:36.760
in the rain were not a dream.

00:11:36.760 --> 00:11:41.170
The fog began to clear and
everything came into focus,

00:11:41.170 --> 00:11:42.800
the mountains, landscape, river,

00:11:42.800 --> 00:11:47.440
and the other villages
were there, unmoved.

00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:50.840
An old man who had been smoking his
pipe behind the [inaudible] emptied

00:11:50.840 --> 00:11:53.040
it and stuffed it in his pockets.

00:11:53.040 --> 00:11:54.670
The ritual began.

00:11:54.670 --> 00:11:57.440
Knives were drawn and the goat
was first stabbed in the stomach

00:11:57.440 --> 00:12:03.840
to summon our ancestors from their
enclaves and then it was meat.

00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:07.340
After some time, an old aunt
came for us, calling for us

00:12:07.340 --> 00:12:09.400
to come out of the house.

00:12:09.400 --> 00:12:10.810
We hugged tightly.

00:12:10.810 --> 00:12:12.890
My sister and I wiped
each other's tears.

00:12:12.890 --> 00:12:17.230
It was only after we had heard her
footsteps approaching our house

00:12:17.230 --> 00:12:21.440
that we walked out, holding hands,
fingers tightly intertwined.

00:12:21.440 --> 00:12:26.710 position:56%
The only way to have torn me away
from her would have to cut us apart.

00:12:26.710 --> 00:12:30.470
The villagers shouted insult at
the thing as it remained unknown

00:12:30.470 --> 00:12:35.420
to them, for what felt like an
entire lifetime, while my sister

00:12:35.420 --> 00:12:37.650
and I sat at [inaudible]
our heads bowed.

00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:39.550
The elders kept referring
to this thing

00:12:39.550 --> 00:12:42.420
as demons and the devil's work.

00:12:42.420 --> 00:12:48.990
None of them knew my
sister, none of them cared.

00:12:48.990 --> 00:12:53.860
The sun was up now, thick shadows
gathering around the house.

00:12:53.860 --> 00:12:55.310
Even though there was no wind,

00:12:55.310 --> 00:12:58.760
the windmill by the fields
made a creaking sound.

00:12:58.760 --> 00:13:04.070
My mother was torn and defeated and
questioned why God gave this thing

00:13:04.070 --> 00:13:07.580
to my sister and my father.

00:13:07.580 --> 00:13:12.070
Secrets stay buried for so long
but one day they rise to open

00:13:12.070 --> 00:13:15.040
like seeds breaking
free from the earth.

00:13:15.040 --> 00:13:18.480
Nobody had ever mentioned
that my father had this thing,

00:13:18.480 --> 00:13:22.250
that he had left one day on his
horse to see distant relatives

00:13:22.250 --> 00:13:28.080
and had never come back, to only
be see in a way that [inaudible]

00:13:28.080 --> 00:13:31.150
after their death in
dreams in hallucinations.

00:13:31.150 --> 00:13:36.240
He had been seen in some village
at least twice, my mother told me.

00:13:36.240 --> 00:13:38.810
The person who had seen
him yelled and waved

00:13:38.810 --> 00:13:41.100
but he never bothered to look.

00:13:41.100 --> 00:13:42.620
They were not sure
if it was my father

00:13:42.620 --> 00:13:45.910
but they were convinced
that it had to be.

00:13:45.910 --> 00:13:50.160
He was never buried, though
it is now 20 years later.

00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:52.980
There was nothing to bury.

00:13:52.980 --> 00:13:54.490
I have no memory of my father.

00:13:54.490 --> 00:13:57.760
There was always hope that he
would return from somewhere.

00:13:57.760 --> 00:14:00.560
Nobody knew where, nobody
cared as long as he returned.

00:14:00.560 --> 00:14:07.260
The night of the ritual, my sister
and I slept lying the same way

00:14:07.260 --> 00:14:08.940
and stared off in different
directions.

00:14:08.940 --> 00:14:13.680
I woke up and she was
holding me, squeezing me,

00:14:13.680 --> 00:14:17.910
and she had sunk her teeth into
the pillow so she would not cry.

00:14:17.910 --> 00:14:21.790
She [inaudible] for a few minutes
and then fell asleep in my arms.

00:14:21.790 --> 00:14:26.140
In the morning, I went
to milk the goat.

00:14:26.140 --> 00:14:31.590
I saw two human shadows
hovering above the [inaudible].

00:14:31.590 --> 00:14:36.090
At first, though it was unusual,
I thought nothing of it even

00:14:36.090 --> 00:14:38.670
as they mumbled something
to each other.

00:14:38.670 --> 00:14:42.880
In the shadows that lived inside
the [inaudible], with the smell

00:14:42.880 --> 00:14:46.570
of manure, I saw that it was my
mother and an uncle who had come

00:14:46.570 --> 00:14:49.130
to stay with us for the ritual.

00:14:49.130 --> 00:14:51.830
It was as if their heads
were bound together into one,

00:14:51.830 --> 00:14:55.400 position:56%
creating a giant head, a ghost even.

00:14:55.400 --> 00:14:58.930
I had meant to get out, but when
I heard them mention my sister,

00:14:58.930 --> 00:15:01.590
I put the jug of milk
down and crouched,

00:15:01.590 --> 00:15:04.970
leaning on the goat
so it did not move.

00:15:04.970 --> 00:15:06.910
My father [inaudible],
the man who had moved

00:15:06.910 --> 00:15:11.960
in with my mother were making
plans to take my sister away.

00:15:11.960 --> 00:15:16.070
The medication and the ritual
did not work, my mother said.

00:15:16.070 --> 00:15:19.860
The way she saw it, my sister
needed to see [inaudible].

00:15:19.860 --> 00:15:22.970
This thing is going to
come back, she said.

