in film school were about,

00:24:26.550 --> 00:24:33.390
because a lot of violence in
South Africa happens to lesbians.

00:24:33.390 --> 00:24:37.300
There's a very terrible
thing called corrective rape

00:24:37.300 --> 00:24:42.620
so that's what the film was
about but more than that,

00:24:42.620 --> 00:24:47.730
the film was really looking at
a society that allows a society

00:24:47.730 --> 00:24:51.250
where corrective rape happens so
that's what the film was about

00:24:51.250 --> 00:24:53.630
and this is why it's been
really difficult to write

00:24:53.630 --> 00:24:58.470
because for me it's not just
the subject but it's important

00:24:58.470 --> 00:25:01.530
for everything about it
to kind of fit perfectly

00:25:01.530 --> 00:25:07.900
into both my own politics but also
for the film to go against the sort

00:25:07.900 --> 00:25:12.600
of very problematic descriptions
or problematic conversations

00:25:12.600 --> 00:25:16.090
that have gone on around
corrective rape.

00:25:16.090 --> 00:25:19.670
&gt;&gt; What does that mean,
corrective rape?

00:25:19.670 --> 00:25:27.770 position:56%
&gt;&gt; I mean you know, the way to
describe it is that there's the idea

00:25:27.770 --> 00:25:33.760
that if a bunch of men
decide to rape a lesbian,

00:25:33.760 --> 00:25:38.020
gang rape a lesbian it's called
corrective rape because the idea is

00:25:38.020 --> 00:25:43.670
that you cannot be a lesbian so we
will show you that you are a woman,

00:25:43.670 --> 00:25:46.300
and this is why it's
called corrective rape

00:25:46.300 --> 00:25:50.830
because in their mind it's the idea
that you will then become a woman

00:25:50.830 --> 00:25:54.420
as they describe and see it.

