00:26:57.470 --> 00:27:02.470
of them don't have
electricity people use candles

00:27:02.470 --> 00:27:09.550
and what happens often is there's
usually fires and people die.

00:27:09.550 --> 00:27:13.850
I mean, I remember one in
2011, which happened right

00:27:13.850 --> 00:27:18.750
on New Year's Eve when people
were going out to celebrate 2011,

00:27:18.750 --> 00:27:20.250
people were dying in their houses

00:27:20.250 --> 00:27:25.370
and about a month ago there
was another in Cape Town again,

00:27:25.370 --> 00:27:30.620
which happened in an interesting
place where it's called,

00:27:30.620 --> 00:27:34.810
I mean the place is called
[inaudible] and it's in Hout Bay.

00:27:34.810 --> 00:27:41.440
I mean, it sits right next
to the very big mansions

00:27:41.440 --> 00:27:47.140
of rich white people in Cape Town,
so I was really interested in sort

00:27:47.140 --> 00:27:49.190
of like, that relationship
between people who live

00:27:49.190 --> 00:27:53.160
in these very lavish houses
and people who live in shacks

00:27:53.160 --> 00:27:58.130 position:56%
and who live in poverty and these
houses that they really try to build

00:27:58.130 --> 00:28:00.050
and get things together
without any money

00:28:00.050 --> 00:28:02.930
and then it gets destroyed
overnight.

00:28:02.930 --> 00:28:07.070
The short story I'm
