00:35:26.880 --> 00:35:29.940
&gt;&gt; Okay, well thank you,
thank you very much.

00:35:29.940 --> 00:35:34.160
I think we should open
the floor for questions.

00:35:40.060 --> 00:35:43.340
&gt;&gt; Thank you, I really enjoyed
hearing part of your story

00:35:43.340 --> 00:35:45.140
and I'll finish reading it.

00:35:45.140 --> 00:35:51.160 position:56%
My question to you is you talk about
South Africa, how it's considered

00:35:51.160 --> 00:35:54.660
to be possession that causes
mental illness and a lot

00:35:54.660 --> 00:35:58.410
of other African cultures it seems
to be continent-wide there seems

00:35:58.410 --> 00:36:01.400
to be a denial of mental illness

00:36:01.400 --> 00:36:06.520
and therefore a reluctance
to treat it as such.

00:36:06.520 --> 00:36:09.880
Do you feel that writing
about it is going to,

00:36:09.880 --> 00:36:12.800
you as an African writer writing
about mental illness existing

00:36:12.800 --> 00:36:19.000
within the African community will
make it a little bit more accepted

00:36:19.000 --> 00:36:26.810
and also lead people to look
at it as an illness rather

00:36:26.810 --> 00:36:32.220
than a spiritual possession or
even worse, non-existent at all?

00:36:34.610 --> 00:36:41.410
&gt;&gt; I mean, that's I suppose a very
difficult question to answer for me

00:36:41.410 --> 00:36:45.440
because I mean, I wrote the story
because I was really concerned

00:36:45.440 --> 00:36:48.050
about the conversations
that people were having

00:36:48.050 --> 00:36:53.380
around mental illness more so in
my own community in the villages

00:36:53.380 --> 00:36:58.320
so the idea was to really bring
that conversation right into sort

00:36:58.320 --> 00:37:02.380
of people's everyday life and my
idea was that if I write the story,

00:37:02.380 --> 00:37:04.820
people are going to read
it and perhaps we are going

00:37:04.820 --> 00:37:07.420
to have this conversation and
I think that's where it begins,

00:37:07.420 --> 00:37:11.730
it begins with openly having the
conversation and then we can begin

00:37:11.730 --> 00:37:14.050
to kind of change how
society sees it.

00:37:14.050 --> 00:37:17.390
The problem is that
no one talks about it.

00:37:17.390 --> 00:37:19.640
I mean the story of the
government for example,

00:37:19.640 --> 00:37:24.360 position:56%
that decision was made purely on the
idea that what are you going to do

00:37:24.360 --> 00:37:25.800
with mentally ill people?

00:37:25.800 --> 00:37:29.300
You can do whatever, because these
people were taken from the hospital

00:37:29.300 --> 00:37:33.750
and they were given to [inaudible]
that have no experience at all.

00:37:33.750 --> 00:37:37.070
I mean, the horrific stories is
that they were even picked up in,

00:37:37.070 --> 00:37:41.360
they were thrown into vans and just
driven out to the villages so part

00:37:41.360 --> 00:37:44.580
of my idea with the story was
to do the opposite of that,

00:37:44.580 --> 00:37:47.670
was to get people to talk
about it and hopefully once

00:37:47.670 --> 00:37:49.680
that conversation begins
we can let it begin to come

00:37:49.680 --> 00:37:51.980
up with a number of solutions.

00:37:58.350 --> 00:37:59.650
&gt;&gt; Thank you very much.

00:37:59.650 --> 00:38:06.350 position:56%
Your story is very inspiring and you
made me think of different things,

00:38:06.350 --> 00:38:10.260
so what are other subjects
that are not talked

00:38:10.260 --> 00:38:17.750 position:56%
about that should be talked about in
literature that you feel as a writer

00:38:17.750 --> 00:38:20.890
that should be addressed
and are not being addressed?

00:38:20.890 --> 00:38:23.810
And I don't mean necessarily
only in South Africa,

00:38:23.810 --> 00:38:28.000
it could be in the United States,
it could be in any other part

00:38:28.000 --> 00:38:32.480
of the world that you
feel should be addressed.

00:38:32.480 --> 00:38:35.250
&gt;&gt; Oh jeez, I mean I don't know.

00:38:35.250 --> 00:38:41.750
I mean, I work on an I suppose
story to story basis and you know,

00:38:41.750 --> 00:38:43.950
when I was writing about
mental illness it was something

00:38:43.950 --> 00:38:47.950
that I was really thinking
about and when I wrote the film

00:38:47.950 --> 00:38:49.580
that I'm continuing to write

00:38:49.580 --> 00:38:52.580
because that's something I
was really concerned about,

00:38:52.580 --> 00:38:56.020
so I'm not quite sure what else
I could write about in the future

00:38:56.020 --> 00:39:00.250
but I certainly know that
one of the interesting things

00:39:00.250 --> 00:39:02.830
for me being a village
child is that when you come

00:39:02.830 --> 00:39:05.760
to the city there's a
lot of cultural issues,

00:39:05.760 --> 00:39:08.870
a lot of cultural indifference
that you sort of have

00:39:08.870 --> 00:39:13.670
to reconcile your own beliefs and
kind of the way the city operates

00:39:13.670 --> 00:39:17.640 position:56%
so a lot of my writing is
concerned with that, how do you come

00:39:17.640 --> 00:39:21.320
to the city and how much of you
changes and how much of you remains

00:39:21.320 --> 00:39:24.120
and what do you become, so
those are some of the things

00:39:24.120 --> 00:39:25.920
that I want to write about.

00:39:25.920 --> 00:39:28.990
I think part of the one thing I
can tell you about that novel is

00:39:28.990 --> 00:39:35.870
that it has a bit of that.

00:39:35.870 --> 00:39:38.960
&gt;&gt; As an artist that practices
a lot of different art forms,

00:39:38.960 --> 00:39:43.710
how do you make the decision to
put the story that you're thinking

00:39:43.710 --> 00:39:46.010
about into writing, versus
film, versus photography?

00:39:51.540 --> 00:39:54.680
&gt;&gt; I mean, I don't know
how I make that decision.

00:39:54.680 --> 00:40:00.040
I mean, part of it is really
just convenience right?

00:40:00.040 --> 00:40:05.460 position:56%
I have no idea how I would visually
make anything out of mental illness.

00:40:05.460 --> 00:40:10.110
I do not see myself taking my
camera and invading people's spaces

00:40:10.110 --> 00:40:14.410
like that and making that film but
it felt more comfortable for me

00:40:14.410 --> 00:40:17.120
to think about my own community
where I come from in the villages

00:40:17.120 --> 00:40:20.700
and write that so a lot
of, I mean it comes to that

00:40:20.700 --> 00:40:24.870
and sometimes I mean, I was
in Tanzania before I came here

00:40:24.870 --> 00:40:29.290
and there's a big fishing
community in Tanzania

00:40:29.290 --> 00:40:32.360
and I made some really
interesting images there

00:40:32.360 --> 00:40:38.510 position:56%
but I didn't write anything about it
so it really depends on what works

00:40:38.510 --> 00:40:41.280
at that time and so what
time is available to me

00:40:41.280 --> 00:40:44.450
because at the time I was in
Tanzania, I was writing a story

00:40:44.450 --> 00:40:48.170
so I didn't have the time to write
another but I could make the images

00:40:48.170 --> 00:40:50.920
so it really works in that way.

00:40:57.180 --> 00:41:05.060
